CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1941, pg. 10, reads: "Party Marks Fifth Birthday - When little Miss Alto Ray Pratt reached her fifth birthday last week, her parents, Mr. and Mrs. R. Pratt, 2457 Chauncey Drive, invited a group of her youthful friends in for a special party. From the above photo, all seemed to have a good time.  Left to right are: First row, Juanita Ccrawley, Audry Pratt,  Alto Pratt, Richard Anderson, Rubi Plumer. Second row, left to right, Nada Turner, Donald Richardson and Louise Plumer. (Harris Photo)"
TitMainTitle: Juanita Crawley, Audry Pratt, Richard Anderson and Rubi Plumer left to right in first row, with Alto Ray Pratt wearing button inscribed "5..." holding birthday cake, and Nada Turner, Donald Richardson and Louise Plumer from left to right in back row, in Pratt home on 2457 Chauncey, another version
